HEADWORD: pe-tsai
<hw>pe-tsai</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A plant with an elongated celerylike
head of broadstalked leaves used as a vegetable in east Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Chinese cabbage, celery cabbage, napa, <spn>Brassica
rapa</spn> <varn>pekinensis</varn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
